Weeks 1-17

• Bottom 6/7 PROE teams eliminated from playoffs

NYG: 24th, -4.9%

#nflverse https://t.co/z5MseA9GpX

NFL Cornerback Receiving Yards allowed per Target vs. Forced Incompletion Rate (data from @PFF):

- Sauce Gardner is ridiculous, DROY without a doubt
- Ravens secondary has struggled
- Darious Williams was an underrated offseason signing by the Jags

#nflverse https://t.co/Ahqs5jspfq

Pillboxes, people!! Chiefs offense vs Seahawks. Pacheco lead in snaps for the first time in 3 weeks. Watson still getting #2 WR snaps, for #reasons, I guess. The Skyy was apparently WAY too high a ceiling for Moore this year....

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/BDvHCGhoIZ

Defense. Watson outsnapped Williams this week, after having his snaps increased the last two weeks. Cook got more run than normal, too. Took some of Gay's snaps. Harris with only 2 total snaps. Williams with a season LOW, and Shelton with a season high. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/LpTNfIwLGD

Here's Seattle's numbers. That is some REAL weirdness in their OLINE numbers. No clue what's going on there. Probably more to glean here, but I'm not a Seahawks fan. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/vlUj4MHizd

If anyone wants to look at our Kaggle, it is here: https://t.co/w5Zx8gLrWD. If you have any questions, please ask. Thank you once again to the NFL for hosting this competition each year, especially to @StatsbyLopez and @DataWithBliss , among others.
